    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Secretary of State to General
                        of the Army Douglas MacArthur, at Tokyo</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1947v06</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d297</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">297</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1947-02-13T18:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1947-02-13T18:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-02-13T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-02-13T18:00:00-05:00" n="297" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d297">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 PW/2–1347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to General
                        of the Army <persName type="to">Douglas MacArthur</persName>, at Tokyo</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-02-13T18:00:00-05:00">February 13, 1947—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>48. Personal for General MacArthur from Ambassador Atcheson. Understand that
                    advanced transfer paper introduced today in <gloss target="#t_FEC1">FEC</gloss>
                    against background of US Govt decision to issue interim directive if Commission
                    does not act favorably on paper in question within approximately 2 weeks.<note n="35" xml:id="d297fn35">For report on action taken, see telegram 54 (<gloss target="#t_FEC1">FEC</gloss> 8), February 19, to Tokyo, <ref target="#pg_359">p. 359</ref>.</note> [Atcheson.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
